    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER SERIES - REMOVE - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302504">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302504" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302504" filename="../figg13/G1302504.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Remove Retaining Bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two bolts and the tension spring cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302505">Figure 5</hotlnk>)
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302505" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302505" filename="../figg13/G1302505.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 5. Remove Bolts and Tension Spring Cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four tension springs (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302506">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302506" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302506" filename="../figg13/G1302506.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 6. Remove Tension Springs</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Jar housing lightly to break gasket seal and lift housing from the transmission (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302507">Figure 7</hotlnk>). Tip housing over to remove four balls in the tension
                spring bores (inset).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302507" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302507" filename="../figg13/G1302507.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 7. Lift Housing From Transmission</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
